  "prompt": "What are the new features in iPhone 7?",
  "response": "The iPhone 7, released in September 2016, introduced several new features and improvements over its predecessors. Here are some of the key enhancements:\n\n1. **Design**: The iPhone 7 retained the overall design language of the iPhone 6s but introduced new color options, including Jet Black and Black.\n\n2. **Water and Dust Resistance**: The iPhone 7 is rated IP67, making it resistant to dust and water (up to 1 meter for 30 minutes).\n\n3. **Home Button**: The physical home button was replaced with a solid-state button that uses haptic feedback to simulate the feel of a button press.\n\n4. **Camera Improvements**:\n   - The iPhone 7 has a 12-megapixel rear camera with a larger aperture (f/1.8) for better low-light performance.\n   - Optical image stabilization (OIS) is included to reduce blurriness in photos and videos.\n   - The front-facing camera was upgraded to 7 megapixels for higher quality selfies and video calls.\n\n5. **Removal of Headphone Jack**: Apple removed the traditional 3.5mm headphone jack, encouraging users to adopt wireless audio solutions or use the Lightning port with an adapter.\n\n6. **Stereo Speakers**: The iPhone 7 introduced stereo speakers for improved audio playback, with one speaker located at the bottom and another at the top of the device.\n\n7. **A10 Fusion Chip**: The iPhone 7 is powered by the A10 Fusion chip, a quad-core processor that offers improved performance and efficiency compared to previous models.\n\n8. **Display**: The Retina HD display saw improvements, including a wider color gamut (P3) for more vibrant and true-to-life colors.\n\n9. **Increased Storage Options**: The iPhone 7 offered higher storage capacities, starting at 32GB, and included options for 128GB and 256GB.\n\n10. **Battery Life**: Enhanced battery life due to more efficient hardware and software optimizations.\n\nThese features collectively made the iPhone 7 a significant upgrade from the iPhone 6s, offering better performance, improved camera capabilities, and additional durability.",
